OL,6,FHe said the "career criminal" must
OL,7,Fhave realised Mr Kondor, who was
OL,8,Fwearing a high-viz jacket, was there,
OL,9,Fbut made the choice that the driver
OL,10,Fwas "expendable".
OL,12,FDet Ch Insp Entwistle said: "Claudiu
OL,13,Fwas a decent hard-working man and it's
OL,14,Fclear he was determined not to let
OL,15,FRoss take his livelihood. For half a
OL,16,Fmile he bravely clung to the open door
OL,17,Fas Ross swerved the van around at
OL,18,Fspeed before deliberately crashing
OL,19,Fleaving him fatally injured.
